includes two summary representations in timeseriesbase: an HTML summary and an optional Plotly-based summary. The HTML summary can be accessed just like the Map summary (calling the TimeSeries object in a Jupyter notebook or by using the "quicklook" function). The plotly representation is accessed by calling the "summary" function. This is included to showcase the interactive functionality, but can be moved out of timeseriesbase and into a separate example in the future.

Two tests are included in the test_timeseriesbase for the HTML summary and quicklook functions. Also, three modified source files are included for goes, gbm, and lyra TimeSeries objects. The modifications include two possible new attributes ("_channel", and "_url") that provide the names and wavelengths (or energy ranges) for instrument-specific channels as well as a url to the instrument website. Both of these attributes are used in the summary representations and can be viewed using sample SunPy data for the above sources. 
